WEBVTT

00:05.964 --> 00:07.716
[ekg beeping]

00:40.999 --> 00:42.917
[Karamo] This is his top surgery.

00:43.501 --> 00:45.378
When we say top surgery,

00:45.462 --> 00:47.297
-we mean to get rid of breasts?
-Yes.

00:47.380 --> 00:48.339
[whistles]

00:54.888 --> 00:57.849
[Skyler]
I was born and identified as a woman.

00:58.266 --> 01:02.353
But since I was in preschool,
I've known that that just wasn't me.

01:02.812 --> 01:05.523
I remember when I was 12,
standing in a mirror

01:06.024 --> 01:09.569
and contorting my body in ways
to be more masculine.

01:10.153 --> 01:14.032
Thinking, "I'm gonna get a surgery
that makes me look like this."

01:27.587 --> 01:29.506
[woman] We've finished your surgery.

01:29.589 --> 01:31.132
Wanna take a look quickly?

01:40.350 --> 01:41.559
[all] Aw...

01:42.936 --> 01:45.480
[Karamo] He just looked down
for the first time.

01:47.607 --> 01:48.441
Okay?

01:49.776 --> 01:51.111
[chuckles]

01:53.488 --> 01:54.656
Wow.

01:54.739 --> 01:59.160
We all struggle with the realization
we were different than everyone else.

01:59.244 --> 02:01.996
I can only imagine
how hard it was to realize

02:02.080 --> 02:05.917
you weren't born with the right body.
He was able to come to that realization

02:06.000 --> 02:08.211
and take the steps
to become who he is.

02:08.586 --> 02:10.630
He's an inspiration.

02:13.133 --> 02:14.175
[groans]

02:14.509 --> 02:15.426
Thank you.

02:15.844 --> 02:18.263
I can't wait to meet him.

02:18.346 --> 02:21.558
[Widelife's "All Things
(Just Keep Getting Better)" playing]

02:21.641 --> 02:24.936
♪ All things just keep getting better ♪

02:26.855 --> 02:29.524
[Brocklesby Crooke
&amp; Kairos Kilt's "Be Free" playing]

02:29.607 --> 02:31.651
♪ I never had the chance to be me ♪

02:31.734 --> 02:35.905
♪ I think I really want to be free
I never had the chance to be me ♪

02:35.989 --> 02:38.074
♪ 'Cause all my life, I never could see ♪

02:38.158 --> 02:40.285
♪ You're the only one
That makes me happy ♪

02:40.368 --> 02:43.663
That video was so eye-opening to me

02:43.746 --> 02:45.081
-and so special.
-Powerful.

02:45.165 --> 02:48.167
[Karamo]
So many gay men, lesbian, bisexual people,

02:48.251 --> 02:51.087
we don't know truly
what the trans experience is.

02:51.170 --> 02:54.382
We support them but
we don't know everything they go through.

02:54.465 --> 02:57.802
I think that, probably,
most straight people assume that,

02:57.886 --> 03:01.973
because it's LGBTQ, we must
all understand each other's plight.

03:02.473 --> 03:04.142
That couldn't be more wrong.

03:04.225 --> 03:07.312
-I've never met a trans person.
-In this car alone,

03:07.395 --> 03:09.480
our five stories are so different.

03:09.564 --> 03:13.401
I'm interested to meet a trans person
to understand their story.

03:14.527 --> 03:17.405
All right,
so I got some more info on Skyler.

03:17.488 --> 03:20.950
As we know Skyler is a transgendered man
who was raised as a female.

03:21.743 --> 03:23.745
Spent most of his life feeling one way,

03:23.828 --> 03:25.955
having the world see him
as something else.

03:26.039 --> 03:29.083
[Skyler] I came to college,
I started doing drag, gave myself

03:29.167 --> 03:33.630
that safe space to explore my gender.
Over a couple of years, I figured out

03:33.713 --> 03:36.132
I didn't wanna be a man
on-stage in drag,

03:36.216 --> 03:38.927
I wanted to be seen
as a man all the time.

03:39.010 --> 03:42.347
-And I eventually had to commit.
-Yeah.

03:42.430 --> 03:45.475
For the last eight years,
Skyler has used most of his money

03:45.558 --> 03:48.811
and energy preparing for top surgery.
He got it six weeks ago.

03:49.395 --> 03:52.982
It definitely drove a big wedge

03:53.066 --> 03:54.359
in my family.

03:54.609 --> 03:59.280
They came to a point where they thought
that I needed to be put away,

03:59.364 --> 04:03.034
that I was insane for thinking
that I could ever be a man.

04:03.117 --> 04:05.828
And that was really hard

04:06.371 --> 04:10.833
to have my mom and my dad say
those type of hurtful things to me.

04:10.917 --> 04:14.879
I had to cut ties with them, and
that was a decision I had to make.

04:14.963 --> 04:18.633
It was very difficult
but it was the right decision for me.

04:19.342 --> 04:23.054
Skyler is excited to start the next
chapter of his life but he needs help.

04:23.137 --> 04:26.432
I think from this experience,
Skyler needs confidence

04:26.516 --> 04:29.602
in his new identity
and to have somebody say:

04:29.686 --> 04:33.815
"We're gonna make you the best you
you can be, and you do belong."

04:33.898 --> 04:35.900
That could change everything.

04:36.192 --> 04:37.610
Up until very recently,

04:37.694 --> 04:39.654
my sole focus was top surgery.

04:39.737 --> 04:43.658
Now that I have that burden
lifted off of me, I actually can think

04:43.741 --> 04:47.453
about the ways that spending time
with these guys could benefit me.

04:47.537 --> 04:48.788
It's really exciting.

04:48.871 --> 04:50.581
Skyler has always worn clothes

04:50.665 --> 04:53.543
that do not fit his body
to hide his curves

04:53.626 --> 04:55.128
he wasn't comfortable with.

04:55.211 --> 04:57.630
But he also loves to stand out
in the crowd.

04:58.298 --> 05:01.467
Skyler is a ginger,
and his hair and beard define him.

05:01.551 --> 05:03.636
-I want us to unpack that a bit.
-Yeah.

05:04.137 --> 05:07.682
My beard has taken two to three years
to fully grow in.

05:07.765 --> 05:10.476
Being a transgender man,
no one taught me how to shave.

05:10.810 --> 05:13.604
I didn't have a dad or an older brother

05:13.688 --> 05:17.233
that was gonna show me
how to do it and not hurt myself.

05:17.317 --> 05:20.278
Skyler has an open-door policy
and loves having people over.

05:20.486 --> 05:23.114
He takes in a lot of people
who have been displaced.

05:23.197 --> 05:26.451
His friends in the LGBTQ community
helped him fundraise

05:26.534 --> 05:28.536
over 8 grand for his top surgery.

05:28.619 --> 05:29.996
That's what we do.

05:30.455 --> 05:32.749
He wants to say
thank you to all his friends

05:32.832 --> 05:36.335
for helping him out. He wants
to throw a big event this weekend.

05:36.419 --> 05:38.963
-What a champion.
-Guys, our mission this week,

05:39.047 --> 05:41.674
it's to help Skyler
become the man he was born to be.

05:41.758 --> 05:42.967
-Yeah.
-Sounds great.

05:43.051 --> 05:44.510
I'm down for that.

05:51.809 --> 05:53.061
-Open up.
-We're here.

05:53.144 --> 05:55.229
Hello, Skyler.

05:55.313 --> 05:56.939
-Hi.
-Hey.

05:57.482 --> 05:58.941
-Skyler.
-I'm Bobby.

05:59.025 --> 06:00.443
What's going on, man?

06:00.526 --> 06:01.569
-Hi.
-Hey, Skyler.

06:01.652 --> 06:05.031
-I'm Tan, nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you. I'm Skyler.

06:05.114 --> 06:08.201
-Hi, how you doing, buddy?
-I'm good, how are you?

06:08.493 --> 06:11.454
-I love that shirt.
-Thanks. It's a little lace.

06:11.537 --> 06:14.916
Skyler's house screams
queer, queer, queer, queer, queer.

06:14.999 --> 06:17.418
It reminds me of somebody
in their early 20s,

06:17.502 --> 06:20.379
and everything is about being part
of the queer community.

06:20.463 --> 06:24.050
-Why the condoms on your table?
-It's a good centerpiece.

06:24.133 --> 06:26.385
This cat life is
everything that I need.

06:26.469 --> 06:29.889
-[Karamo] Why so many couches?
-[Mary Lou] A lot of people come over.

06:29.972 --> 06:33.059
Got it. They look the worst.
What's underneath here?

06:33.267 --> 06:34.727
Oh!

06:35.228 --> 06:37.563
That's the cat pee couch.

06:37.939 --> 06:39.774
[Karamo] Skyler, Skyler, man.

06:39.857 --> 06:41.359
-No, seriously?
-[laughs]

06:41.442 --> 06:42.401
A cat pee couch?

06:42.485 --> 06:43.486
-Really?
-I know.

06:43.569 --> 06:46.072
-It's a full cat pee couch?
-[Skyler] I know.

06:46.739 --> 06:47.740
I'm kitty.

06:47.824 --> 06:49.826
Once they start,
they only pee on it.

06:49.909 --> 06:52.245
This is the most disgusting thing
ever.

06:52.328 --> 06:53.162
[purring]

06:53.246 --> 06:57.041
-[Skyler] You came with your own gloves?
-This is actually a Magnum condom.

06:57.125 --> 06:59.085
Bobber's out of control.

06:59.168 --> 07:00.503
Naughty kitty.

07:00.586 --> 07:02.171
Oh!

07:02.964 --> 07:03.798
I was too big.

07:04.757 --> 07:08.553
Tell me about his, uh, style.

07:09.053 --> 07:12.849
That's one thing
that he is really, like, on top of.

07:12.932 --> 07:14.809
He's a very fashionable man.

07:14.892 --> 07:18.604
-They come to me for advice.
-[Tan] I don't wanna be judgmental,

07:18.688 --> 07:22.108
but on a personal note,
his outfit is wack.

07:22.191 --> 07:24.444
Skyler is 30,

07:24.527 --> 07:28.489
and he's dressed like a skater boy
from, like, 1995.

07:28.739 --> 07:30.324
[Bobby] That's a lot of hats.

07:30.992 --> 07:33.536
Hats are great
on the head but not the wall.

07:33.619 --> 07:36.289
-How would you store them?
-I'm gonna figure that out.

07:36.998 --> 07:38.124
[Antoni] Oh, my.

07:38.583 --> 07:41.461
-Shiny.
-[Jonathan] There is love on these sheets.

07:41.544 --> 07:43.963
This bed looks
like it came out of a dorm.

07:44.046 --> 07:48.134
I need a high bed to store
my second persona underneath it.

07:48.217 --> 07:50.386
-[Tan] Do you wear these shoes?
-A bit.

07:50.470 --> 07:52.930
-[Jonathan] I like those.
-[Tan] The kooky ones

07:53.014 --> 07:55.683
-The other ones are--
-Those are work shoes.

07:55.766 --> 07:59.645
I work at, um, the University of Georgia,
I'm in Events Management.

07:59.729 --> 08:01.981
-[Karamo] Can I ask a question?
-[Skyler] Yes.

08:02.064 --> 08:04.817
You just got out of surgery,
how are you doing?

08:04.901 --> 08:07.695
We're pushing you around,
taking you there, how are you?

08:07.778 --> 08:08.946
I'm doing okay.

08:09.030 --> 08:12.825
This is only the second
time I've worn a tank top post-op,

08:12.909 --> 08:15.453
I can only wear a button-up
so I can't--

08:15.828 --> 08:19.415
That's my range. I can't lift
my arms higher right now.

08:19.499 --> 08:22.668
-When we saw your surgery--
-[Skyler] You guys got to see that?

08:22.752 --> 08:25.296
To see the look in your eyes
when you looked down.

08:25.379 --> 08:26.672
-Yeah.
-Oh, my gosh.

08:26.756 --> 08:29.759
I don't remember a lot of it
because of my complications.

08:29.842 --> 08:32.261
I had a bad reaction
to the anesthesia,

08:32.512 --> 08:35.765
um, which is apparently
really common for redheads.

08:35.848 --> 08:37.183
What?

08:37.266 --> 08:40.895
The MC1R gene in redheads makes you
crazy susceptible

08:40.978 --> 08:43.022
to anesthesias and narcotics.

08:43.105 --> 08:47.318
Um, so, when they put me under,
um, several of my organs shut down.

08:47.401 --> 08:51.197
I have to have another procedure
to address the internal bleeding.

08:51.280 --> 08:54.742
More money? I know you raised
the initial money from the community.

08:54.825 --> 08:55.910
Are you gonna--?

08:55.993 --> 08:59.872
I'm staring at $100,000,
$200,000 hospital bill

08:59.956 --> 09:02.333
in complications for the next year.

09:02.583 --> 09:05.836
So, it really sucks
but I wouldn't change it.

09:06.796 --> 09:09.715
When you see how difficult
his journey has been

09:10.174 --> 09:14.095
but how gracefully he carries himself,
it's inspiring and it's uplifting.

09:14.512 --> 09:15.763
So, how do you feel?

09:16.180 --> 09:17.098
Here we are.

09:18.057 --> 09:20.643
The week is here.
So, how are you feeling?

09:20.935 --> 09:23.437
-I'm excited.
-What's your experience with shaving?

09:23.521 --> 09:25.273
I was never really taught.

09:25.356 --> 09:26.357
Yeah.

09:26.440 --> 09:29.360
I went through my second puberty
in my mid-20s.

09:29.443 --> 09:31.153
-Do you get hair here?
-Yes.

09:31.487 --> 09:33.155
-We get all down here.
-Uh-huh.

09:33.239 --> 09:35.575
-It comes all the way down to here.
-Got it.

09:36.117 --> 09:37.952
I really shy away from imparting

09:38.035 --> 09:40.371
what I believe has
to happen on someone's look.

09:40.454 --> 09:42.123
I like it to be a collaboration,

09:42.206 --> 09:45.126
what does it look
like for you in the morning?

09:45.209 --> 09:48.045
I'm here to help you
be the best you that you can be,

09:48.129 --> 09:51.048
comma, I don't want you to look
like a leprechaun.

09:51.132 --> 09:52.133
We gotta change it.

09:52.550 --> 09:54.051
[Karamo] I'm noticing a theme.

09:54.176 --> 09:58.472
It's like you've kind of been stuck
in, like, "I'm 19, 20 years old."

09:58.556 --> 10:01.058
That's one of the things I struggle with,

10:01.142 --> 10:04.270
that forever young kind of, like,
Peter Pan syndrome,

10:04.353 --> 10:05.479
for sure.

10:05.563 --> 10:09.233
Uh, there's three fictional characters
that describe you,

10:09.317 --> 10:12.778
and Peter Pan is one of them for me
that I always use.

10:12.862 --> 10:14.905
Who would you want
to replace that with?

10:14.989 --> 10:17.950
It would be Todrick.
But he's not fictional.

10:18.034 --> 10:19.744
I love Todrick.

10:19.827 --> 10:21.912
His fashion,
performance, his music.

10:21.996 --> 10:23.789
I'm inspired by everything he does.

10:25.041 --> 10:27.835
When you open up tomato sauce,
you gotta eat it quickly.

10:28.461 --> 10:30.087
[groaning]

10:30.171 --> 10:31.130
That's no bueno.

10:31.213 --> 10:35.134
I commend you for being in a place
where you can take care of others.

10:35.217 --> 10:36.927
How do you find time for yourself?

10:38.262 --> 10:39.263
That's very hard.

10:39.347 --> 10:42.475
Is there anything on your mind
you know you wanna do?

10:42.558 --> 10:44.727
One of the most important things

10:44.810 --> 10:48.022
for me right now, um, is my gender marker.

10:48.314 --> 10:51.067
-It is still female on my license.
-Mm-hm.

10:51.150 --> 10:53.444
Um, and now that I'm actually post-op,

10:53.694 --> 10:57.740
um, I have all of the documents
I need to be able to go to the DMV

10:57.823 --> 11:01.243
and get that taken care of,
get my gender marker changed.

11:01.327 --> 11:03.162
This is what I'm talking about.

11:03.871 --> 11:05.998
Most of us take our IDs for granted.

11:06.082 --> 11:10.211
We got it when we were 15 or 16,
and we never think about it.

11:10.294 --> 11:14.882
But all he wants is to just experience
the same life that we all experience.

11:15.216 --> 11:17.760
This one little thing
is holding him back.

11:18.344 --> 11:20.679
Can you show me
what's going on here?

11:20.763 --> 11:22.556
We each have our own pantry.

11:22.640 --> 11:25.643
-This one is mine, the most overflowing.
-[Antoni] Uh-huh.

11:26.352 --> 11:27.978
-Yeah.
-Um, like crazy.

11:28.062 --> 11:29.939
This could use some organization.

11:30.022 --> 11:32.358
There's not that much garbage food.

11:32.441 --> 11:35.945
Like, you eat pretty healthy-ish.
What's your indulgence?

11:36.028 --> 11:37.988
-Something that feels good--
-Sushi.

11:38.072 --> 11:40.199
-Sushi?
-Sushi is my favorite food.

11:40.282 --> 11:42.785
-I never can make that at the house.
-Got you.

11:42.868 --> 11:46.080
In a perfect world, how would you see
this space working for you?

11:46.163 --> 11:49.500
-Obviously, lots of seating for family.
-Yes. Yeah.

11:49.583 --> 11:51.377
Lots of seating, comfortable.

11:51.460 --> 11:54.213
I like that this is a space, too,

11:54.296 --> 11:58.008
where the second people walk in,
even if they're not my friends,

11:58.092 --> 12:00.761
they know they're stepping
into a queer space.

12:00.845 --> 12:03.931
I want Skyler to realize
that queer is just a column,

12:04.140 --> 12:07.268
a column
that holds up the house of Skyler.

12:07.351 --> 12:09.437
Yes, he needs to be proud.

12:09.645 --> 12:13.149
But flags are to be flown,
they're not décor.

12:14.150 --> 12:17.361
-This is a much younger person's look.
-[chuckles]

12:17.445 --> 12:19.697
-People think I'm early 20s.
-Teenager.

12:19.780 --> 12:21.532
And it's my look and my look.

12:21.615 --> 12:23.367
Yes. I want you to look like

12:23.451 --> 12:26.245
a 30-something-year-old man
who's ready to move forward.

12:26.328 --> 12:29.790
I have noticed
that your stuff is kind of androgynous.

12:29.874 --> 12:34.336
Yes. I actually made that to wear to
Todrick's, um, Straight Outta Oz concert.

12:34.420 --> 12:36.505
I'm the worst gay of them all.

12:36.589 --> 12:39.425
And I don't even know
who this Todrick person is.

12:39.508 --> 12:42.386
Todrick Hall is a YouTube star.
Very openly gay.

12:42.845 --> 12:44.889
I'm inspired by his music, his style.

12:44.972 --> 12:48.559
He likes playing with fashion and
femininity. Your top is feminine.

12:48.642 --> 12:51.103
-I like it.
-Super feminine. Thank you so much.

12:51.353 --> 12:53.063
Until now, I've been intimidated,

12:53.147 --> 12:57.443
thinking I don't know what I'm gonna put
him in, I want him to feel like a dude.

12:57.651 --> 12:59.361
Now, I couldn't care less.

12:59.445 --> 13:02.907
I'm gonna find out who
this Todrick person is and we'll try--

13:02.990 --> 13:04.700
Look at his red carpet looks.

13:04.783 --> 13:07.745
He plays with masculine,
and feminine, I love that.

13:07.828 --> 13:10.581
He's not confined
to any genre of clothing.

13:10.789 --> 13:14.043
This gives me an opportunity
to play like never before.

13:14.126 --> 13:17.046
I just wanna make sure he feels great
as Skyler.

13:17.129 --> 13:19.965
-You've got so many ties.
-Yes.

13:20.049 --> 13:22.718
A lot of those need to go,
they have stains--

13:22.801 --> 13:25.679
-Almost all are gonna go.
-I have to wear those at work.

13:25.763 --> 13:29.266
-You wear a tie to work?
-Yes. I bought two suits

13:29.350 --> 13:32.102
-that are hanging there.
-I did notice.

13:32.186 --> 13:36.315
When they were trying to tailor
them, I got, like, super uncomfortable

13:36.607 --> 13:38.400
and just kind of panicked and left,

13:38.692 --> 13:41.153
um, because they were getting all up
in my pants

13:41.237 --> 13:43.489
-and in areas and, like, you know.
-Oh...

13:43.572 --> 13:45.699
That's a safety issue for me.

13:45.783 --> 13:48.911
So I've had those
since Christmas and never worn them.

13:48.994 --> 13:49.912
Okay.

13:49.995 --> 13:52.498
I don't know
what they would need to be sized for.

13:52.581 --> 13:56.919
Nothing makes me feel like more
of a guy than when I'm in a suit.

13:57.127 --> 13:58.629
-Okay. Mm-hm.
-A good suit.

13:58.712 --> 14:01.549
That's the height
of sophistication for a man.

14:01.799 --> 14:04.760
So, I kind of wanna find a way to get you
in a suit

14:04.843 --> 14:07.346
-that makes complete sense for you.
-Okay.

14:07.429 --> 14:10.683
I will get you fun options
but let's get the basics down.

14:10.766 --> 14:13.185
-The basics of a man's wardrobe is a suit.
-Yeah.

14:13.811 --> 14:15.729
-Yeah?
-I agree with you on that.

14:16.021 --> 14:17.398
Okay, good. Good.

14:17.481 --> 14:18.566
[meows]

14:18.649 --> 14:21.068
You have an event coming up.
Tell us about it?

14:21.151 --> 14:24.905
Yes. I am six weeks out post-op
from top surgery today.

14:24.989 --> 14:27.741
-Um, so, that's really exciting.
-Yes.

14:27.992 --> 14:31.078
Um, so, we're gonna go to MSR,

14:31.328 --> 14:33.747
um, which is, like, my home-based bar
in Atlanta.

14:33.831 --> 14:36.458
These are the people that helped me...

14:37.626 --> 14:39.253
change my life.

14:39.837 --> 14:43.382
You know, without all of them
kind of rallying behind me

14:43.465 --> 14:47.136
over the last few months, I wouldn't
have been able to get my top surgery.

14:47.845 --> 14:50.472
On Friday,
I just wanna be able to be visible

14:50.556 --> 14:53.934
and be present and let everybody know
that I'm okay, I'm alive.

14:54.018 --> 14:57.396
And I'm thankful
for all that they've done to me,

14:57.479 --> 14:59.565
help me meet this huge financial goal

14:59.648 --> 15:01.609
that I wouldn't have been able to meet.

