16:47.798 --> 16:50.968
I was having a really hard time.
I got into alcohol

16:51.260 --> 16:53.637
and started doing stuff
that I shouldn't.

16:53.721 --> 16:56.265
One of my friends was living
with us.

16:56.348 --> 16:57.975
She had her own issues at home.

16:58.058 --> 17:00.769
My mom freaked and was like,
"Your friend has to leave,

17:00.853 --> 17:02.563
your friend's a bad influence."

17:02.646 --> 17:05.691
But my friend was the only one
who knew what was going on.

17:05.774 --> 17:07.943
I was like,
"She has nothing to do with it."

17:08.027 --> 17:10.696
And so,
in a screaming match about all this,

17:10.779 --> 17:13.574
she was like, "Give me a reason,
what's wrong with you."

17:13.657 --> 17:15.325
I was like, "I'm gay. I'm gay.

17:15.409 --> 17:19.997
And, like, everyone is making
my life frigging miserable now at school."

17:21.290 --> 17:23.208
And my mom just kind of lost it.

17:23.292 --> 17:26.295
And instead of making my friend go,
I did instead.

17:26.378 --> 17:27.713
-Um...
-Wow.

17:28.255 --> 17:30.966
I've been down this road before,
worried about my past,

17:31.050 --> 17:33.218
worried about the people in my past.

17:33.302 --> 17:37.473
One day, I just had to realize who cares
if your past doesn't come along with you.

17:37.890 --> 17:40.517
You only need your present
and your future.

17:41.268 --> 17:43.062
Skyler's future is bright.

17:43.562 --> 17:45.814
I was outed at 16. I left at 15.

17:45.898 --> 17:49.109
l left, actually,
before my family knew I was gay.

17:49.193 --> 17:50.027
-Yeah.
-Um...

17:50.110 --> 17:52.196
-I was always a really angry kid
-Mm-hm.

17:52.488 --> 17:54.823
because every day of my life,
I wore a mask.

17:54.907 --> 17:57.326
So, when you're hearing constantly

17:57.409 --> 18:00.037
from the people
that mean the most to you

18:00.120 --> 18:02.831
-that what you are is awful--
-You're awful.

18:03.082 --> 18:04.917
Yeah, and unacceptable.

18:05.000 --> 18:07.461
-It really does a number on you.
-Yeah.

18:07.544 --> 18:10.714
-So, I was just pissed all the time.
-Yeah.

18:11.590 --> 18:14.551
Skyler and I both have the same connection
of rejection

18:14.635 --> 18:16.470
from family, from friends.

18:16.887 --> 18:20.015
And that can be a hard thing to heal from.

18:21.100 --> 18:23.435
How did you get over that damage?

18:23.519 --> 18:27.147
Know how to forgive them for that?
I don't know if it's possible.

18:27.231 --> 18:29.983
It takes your chosen family,
like you have,

18:30.818 --> 18:33.612
that loves you
and accepts you for who you are.

18:33.987 --> 18:36.824
And it helps you to then accept yourself.

18:38.200 --> 18:41.286
Are you excited to give some stuff away?

18:41.411 --> 18:43.413
Yes, I am super excited.

18:43.747 --> 18:46.458
-All right. Let's get down there.
-Let's do it.

18:46.542 --> 18:49.169
Skyler spent
his entire adult life fighting

18:49.253 --> 18:51.296
to be the man he was born to be.

18:51.505 --> 18:53.465
Now we've hit reset for him.

18:53.549 --> 18:54.925
It's nice to meet you, sir.

18:55.008 --> 18:57.719
I appreciate it.
You guys keep up the good work.

18:57.803 --> 19:00.722
And I can definitely tell that
giving back to the community

19:00.806 --> 19:02.474
that's given him so much is going

19:02.558 --> 19:05.227
-to help Skyler heal.
-[Skyler] Where to next?

19:07.521 --> 19:09.148
