And how--?

22:18.545 --> 22:21.631
How would you feel
if I were to get that wrong?

22:22.632 --> 22:24.051
It does still happen.

22:24.134 --> 22:26.386
I get female pronoun-ed
with the full beard.

22:26.470 --> 22:28.430
That was one of the things, actually...

22:29.473 --> 22:33.310
that was the crappiest part
about my hospital experience,

22:33.560 --> 22:36.146
um, because my gender marker
wasn't changed yet.

22:36.229 --> 22:37.981
So, like, on their charts,

22:38.148 --> 22:42.194
they're reading female, seeing female,
the doctors, nurses, everybody walking in.

22:42.277 --> 22:45.072
And despite the fact
that I have a full beard,

22:45.155 --> 22:48.950
and I'm topless, like,
completely like bare chest and no chest.

22:49.409 --> 22:53.455
And they still wanna call me "she" and
"her" and stuff like that.

22:54.831 --> 22:56.583
And it hurts.

22:57.542 --> 23:01.797
Like, God, I spent almost a decade
of my life being miserable in my body.

23:01.880 --> 23:02.964
Just miserable.

23:03.131 --> 23:06.635
The way it affected me in
the way I interacted with people--

23:06.718 --> 23:09.930
I haven't even felt
comfortable giving hugs in a decade

23:10.013 --> 23:14.351
because I feel people touch my chest
and it makes me so uncomfortable.

23:15.018 --> 23:17.270
I, uh... I feel...

23:18.605 --> 23:20.565
frigging stupid, quite honestly.

23:20.649 --> 23:24.319
I appreciate you trying
to educate yourself, it means a lot.

23:24.528 --> 23:25.987
No, I feel stupid.

23:26.071 --> 23:29.783
I've always looked at trans people
and I've thought,

23:30.325 --> 23:31.493
"Why don't you just--?

23:31.576 --> 23:34.079
It costs so much
and it can be really painful.

23:34.538 --> 23:38.959
Why put yourself through that?
It seems such a traumatic experience."

23:39.042 --> 23:40.127
It's a lot.

23:40.210 --> 23:41.878
I truly didn't understand

23:42.420 --> 23:45.924
what that meant to actually
have the surgery done and feel--

23:46.800 --> 23:48.343
And feel that change.

23:48.426 --> 23:50.720
And when I saw the video of you

23:50.929 --> 23:54.474
when you woke up, I don't really
think you were coherent at the time.

23:54.558 --> 23:57.102
-I don't remember it.
-I don't think you were.

23:57.978 --> 23:59.938
But that shows
how frigging raw it was

24:00.021 --> 24:02.482
when you opened your eyes
and looked down

24:02.566 --> 24:06.069
and you go to reach for your chest.

24:06.570 --> 24:07.445
Um...

24:08.780 --> 24:11.908
That changed it for me. I thought,
"Oh, this is what it means."

24:11.992 --> 24:12.826
Yeah.

24:13.201 --> 24:14.035
Um...

24:14.786 --> 24:17.497
I'm annoyed at myself,
"Why didn't you get involved?

24:17.581 --> 24:22.252
You would have then
understood maybe the trans community."

24:22.335 --> 24:25.964
There are so many people
out there like me, who are ignorant,

24:26.256 --> 24:27.716
who don't understand.

24:27.799 --> 24:30.552
I always felt for the plight
of trans people.

24:30.635 --> 24:34.639
However,
I always thought, "Is it necessary for you

24:34.890 --> 24:38.226
to have this top surgery,
for you to feel like a man?"

24:38.310 --> 24:39.436
For Skyler it was.

24:39.519 --> 24:43.356
The fact I didn't understand that
beforehand makes me feel silly.

24:43.648 --> 24:46.109
This really has helped, truly.

24:48.820 --> 24:52.490
How are you feeling about
getting your license changed?

24:52.574 --> 24:54.701
I'm incredibly excited

24:54.784 --> 24:56.703
but also nervous.

24:56.786 --> 24:59.456
This is my second go
trying to get my marker changed.

24:59.539 --> 25:00.916
-Really?
-Mm-hm.

25:01.291 --> 25:02.792
